{"word":"φοινικίς","slug":"φοινικίς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φοινικίς</b></el> <el>(φοινῑκίς, ίδος, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:φοῖνιξ'><el>φοῖνιξ</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a red</i> or <i>purple cloth</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a red cloak</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <el>φοινικίδ' ὀξεῖαν πάνυ</el> <i>a red cloak</i> as bright as bright can be, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>a red curtain</i> or <i>carpet</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschines'>Aeschin.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b><i>a red flag</i>, <b><a href='S:Lysias'>Lys.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Polybius'>Polyb.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}